25|$|Today, {{the court}} case and {{transcripts}} {{are important to}} historians and forensic neurologists, because of the <b>sworn</b> <b>testimony</b> from multiple witnesses regarding Muybridge's state of mind and past behaviour. The American composer Philip Glass composed an opera, The Photographer, with a libretto {{based in part on}} court transcripts from the case.|$|E
